description: {"blocks":[{"key":"86oo0","text":"This protocol outlines preprocessing, statistical and cluster analyses that were applied in 'Using whole-brain diffusion tensor analysis to  evaluate white matter structural correlates of delayed visuospatial memory and one-week motor skill retention in nondemented older adults: A  preliminary study' (https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0274955). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":303,"length":44}],"data":{}},{"key":"q4ag","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3kgqn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7rc6q","text":"The following software packages are required to follow this protocol: FSL, MRtrix, Advanced Normalization Tools (Github: https://github.com/ANTsX/ANTs). Figures were created via AFNI. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":121,"length":29}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"774DD0B83B6D11EDB7F00A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0274955"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"3F2B2CED207E11ECAF560A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://github.com/ANTsX/ANTs"}}}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"82stu","text":"Double-check if your native and original images are in FLOAT32 and oriented with the MNI.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"12pm3","text":"-Convert to float-","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"437u4","text":"fslmaths dwidata.nii.gz dwi.nii.gz -odt float","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":45}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cjig4","text":"DWI Denoising:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"22q3o","text":"dwidenoise -datatype float32 -noise level_noise.nii.gz [IN] [OUT_denoised]","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3vvm4","text":"dwidenoise -datatype float32 -noise level_noise.nii.gz dwi.nii.gz dwi_denoised.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":85}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cf38i","text":"mrdegibbs [OUT_denoised] [OUT_Gibbs]","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ogng","text":"mrdegibbs dwi_denoised.nii.gz dwi_Gibbs.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":46}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d8j59","text":"need brain – bet doesn’t work as well as dwi2mask","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4pksk","text":"dwi2mask -fslgrad bvecs.txt bvals.txt dwi_Gibbs.nii.gz temp_brain_mask.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":77}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1hq9q","text":"Run ‘nodif_brain_mask.sh’ script [e.g.,bash nodif_brain_mask.sh dwi_Gibbs.nii.gz 4214_52 temp_brain_mask.nii.gz] to get temporary nodif brain masks for eddy.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":39,"length":72}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bh261","text":"Rename both of these nodif files with the prefix ‘dwi_Gibbs_’ e.g., ‘dwi_Gibbs_brain_mask’ for eddy. Delete the ‘temp_brain’ file.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5gsed","text":"Run eddy correction and get rotated vector file","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctr2a","text":"eddy --imain=dwi_Gibbs.nii.gz --mask=dwi_Gibbs_brain_mask.nii.gz --index=index.txt --acqp=acqparams.txt --bvecs=bvecs.txt --bvals=bvals.txt --fwhm=0 --flm=quadratic --slm=linear --out=eddy_unwarped_images --data_is_shelled","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":222}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6np0","text":"Nodif and Brain extraction on the data.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"34rbf","text":"fslroi data.nii.gznodif_data0 1","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":31}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cqhqn","text":"dwi2mask -fslgrad eddy_unwarped_images.eddy_rotated_bvecs.txt bvals.txt data.nii.gz temp_brain_mask.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":106}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5but","text":"Run ‘nodif_brain_mask.sh’ script [e.g.,bash nodif_brain_mask.sh data.nii.gz 4214_52 temp_brain_mask.nii.gz] output is ‘nodif_brain_mask.nii.gz’ and ‘nodif_brain.nii.gz’ rename and add ‘data’ in front, so ‘data_nodif_brain’. Delete ‘temp_brain’ file.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":39,"length":67}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6poh","text":"Bias Field correction (via ANTs):","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":31}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4ienp","text":"dwibiascorrect ants data.nii.gz data_bias.nii.gz -fslgrad eddy_unwarped_images.eddy_rotated_bvecs.txt bvals.txt -mask data_nodif_brain_mask.nii.gz -bias bias_image.nii.gz -ants.b [100,3]","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":186}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1okts","text":"Upsample DWI images for better coregistration with MNI template","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"19r77","text":"mrgrid -vox 1.25 data_bias.nii.gz regrid data_bias_HR.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":60}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"68llj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ca26","text":"Fit tensor model","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f648r","text":"dtifit -k data_bias_HR.nii.gz -o DTI_map_w-linear_ -m nodif_brain_mask.nii.gz -r eddy_unwarped_images.eddy_rotated_bvecs.txt -b bvals.txt -w","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":140}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fq0gg","text":"Optional: create bash script to generate group template","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3qcm1","text":"Copy all the nodif_brain.nii.gz images into one folder and change directory to it. Then run:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3lj7d","text":"bash buildtemplateparallel.sh -d 3 -o template -c 0 -r 1 -n 0 -i 3 *.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":75}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e63vq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4pvc3","text":"WarpImageMultiTransform 3 [in: FA map in native space] [out: FA map in template space] -R templatetemplate.nii.gz [warp file] [affine file] ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":140},{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":140}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"65kpp","text":"At this point all participant FA maps should be in template space. Create a 4D (x,y,z + time) file with all your maps:\nInsert all your FA in template space in one folder and run:\nfslmerge -t [output] *.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":179,"length":29}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1f7kv","text":"Create then apply mask from all subjects","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fho8k","text":"fslmaths all_FA.nii.gz -max 0 -Tmin -bin mean_mask -odt char","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":60}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7t0j0","text":"fslmaths all_FA.nii.gz -mas mean_mask all_FA.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":51}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cvp28","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b72j8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ft10j","text":"Create a mean of the FA over-time and create white matter mask (thresholded at FA\u003e0.20):","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8cdi8","text":"fslmaths all_FA -Tmean mean_FA","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2b9c3","text":"fslmaths mean_FA -thr 0.20 -bin WM_mask","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":39}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9care","text":"Apply  your mask to your smoothed maps:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b8sjh","text":"fslmaths all_FA_smooth -mas mean_mask all_FA_smooth","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":51}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c17c4","text":"At this point you should have a FA map 'all_FA.nii.gz'  for all subjects.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5nj59","text":"Create linear regression script (that applies model voxel-by-voxel) using the LM.m function in MATLAB by using:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a6vg5","text":"LM (file_ID1, raw_image_subject, mask)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ec2k","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5k","text":"e.g., LM (covariates.txt, all_FA_smooth.nii, WM_mask.nii)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":6,"length":51}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"epoob","text":"Resulting files will be the FDR-corrected p-value and tstat maps for each variable.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clusterize and apply white matter atlas to identify clusters
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"e5vfi","text":"Example is for first behavioral variable 'score_1'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"993ut","text":"3dcalc -ascore_1_FDR.nii-expr 'a*1' -prefixscore_1_FDR_corrected.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":71}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fpmsv","text":"3dcalc -a score_1_tStat.nii -expr 'a*1' -prefix score_1_tStat_corrected.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":78}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clusterize and apply white matter atlas to identify clusters
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"86qsu","text":"Split scores tStat into positive and negative (this provides you with positive and negative correlations):","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":105}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8s43","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2uo90","text":"Fslmathsscore_1_tStat_corrected.nii.gz -thr 0 positive_score1.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":68}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b79lk","text":"Fslmathsscore_1_tStat_corrected.nii.gz -uthr 0 negative_score1.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":69}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bgiu9","text":"*For negative images, need to multiply by -1","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"366kn","text":"Fslmaths negative_score1.nii.gz -mul -1 negative_score1.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":62}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clusterize and apply white matter atlas to identify clusters
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4k4nr","text":"Get FDR-corrected p-value clusters that are less than 0.01 and that are at least 100 voxels in size  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"13jvc","text":"3dClusterize -nosum -1Dformat -inset score_1_FDR_corrected.nii.gz -idat 0 -ithr 0 -NN 2 -clust_nvox 100 -1sided RIGHT_TAIL 0.99 -pref_map Clust_mask_motor.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":161}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c0e4c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"affcg","text":"fslmaths Clust_mask_motor.nii.gz -bin Clust_mask_motor.nii.gz","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":61}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clusterize and apply white matter atlas to identify clusters
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"792al","text":"Coregister the template to MNI:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6j4v9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dr49u","text":"antsRegistrationSyN.sh -d 3 -m /Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/group_template/templatetemplate.nii.gz -f /usr/local/fsl/data/standard/MNI152_T1_1mm_brain.nii.gz -o /Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI -t s","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":272}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

Behavioral variables are 'score_1' and 'motor'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"flqu0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"diskb","text":"Transform clusters to MNI:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":10,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"atbdd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"hk2s","text":"antsApplyTransforms -d 3 -i Clust_mask_motor.nii.gz -o Clust_mask_motor_MNI.nii.gz -r/usr/local/fsl/data/standard/MNI152_T1_1mm_brain.nii.gz -t [/Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI1Warp.nii.gz,0]  -t [/Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI0GenericAffine.mat,0] -n NearestNeighbor","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":380}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1vbk5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6ghsp","text":"Transform scores tstat (positive and negative) to MNI space:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":10,"length":13}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2dhj1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"68vf0","text":"antsApplyTransforms -d 3 -ipositive_score1.nii.gz-opositive_score1_MNI.nii.gz -r/usr/local/fsl/data/standard/MNI152_T1_1mm_brain.nii.gz -t [/Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI1Warp.nii.gz,0]  -t [/Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI0GenericAffine.mat,0]","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":356}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a9g5j","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ala7","text":"antsApplyTransforms -d 3 -inegative_score1.nii.gz-onegative_score1_MNI.nii.gz -r/usr/local/fsl/data/standard/MNI152_T1_1mm_brain.nii.gz -t [/Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI1Warp.nii.gz,0]  -t [/Users/syschaef/Desktop/4214_DTI/MRtrix_preproc/template_to_MNI/templatetemplate_to_MNI0GenericAffine.mat,0]","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":356}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
